    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Rat Rock Continues To Live Up to Its Name</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ronald T Thomson letter on Setpember 24 article notes residents around Columbia University's Rat Rock are still plagued by rats (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''The Rock That Gives New York Its Face'' (Sept. 24), you wrote that local residents ''were plagued for decades by rats nesting'' in Rat Rock. We are still plagued. Removing the rock may cost ''hundreds of thousands of dollars,'' but if Columbia University would spend only a minuscule fraction of that amount on rodent control, we might be able to call it the Rock Formerly Known as Rat.</p>
        <p>RONALD T. THOMSON  Morningside Heights</p>
      </block>
